rdf:Description.lla:note: The name of the previous ship is possibly the 'Charles H Oulton'.

There is a note in the official log stating that on 6/12/1873, S. Classe, William Roberts, John Martins and Heinrich Feine took the boat and left the ship about midnight and did not return, and were considered to have deserted.

There is a receipt for the wages and effects of a deceased seaman attached to the record, but with no identifying name thereon. It it possible that the Master died at Antwerp in between voyages, because the crewmen appear to have been officially discharged and paid off by an official from the British Consulate at Antwerp, in place of the Master, and a new Master is present on the subsequent record for the return voyage from Antwerp.
The previous vessel is possibly the 'Annie Maude' of Aberystwyth.
